Notes on third-party components:

1. The Gemma 4 E2B-it model (Google DeepMind) is the host model required to
   run any of this project's trained artefacts. Gemma 4 is governed by the
   Gemma Terms of Use (https://ai.google.dev/gemma/terms). Any
   redistribution or derivative use of the Gemma model weights themselves,
   separately from this code, must comply with that license. This repository
   does NOT redistribute Gemma weights; users must download Gemma 4 E2B-it
   directly from Google (HuggingFace / Kaggle) and accept the Gemma Terms.

2. The trained AMRSTrace prefix weights (`neko/weights/meow_signature.pt`),
   the LoRA adapter (`leetcode233/weights/phase28a_lora_weights.pt`), and
   the delta weights (`leetcode233/weights/phase28[bcd]_deltas.pt`) are
   small standalone nn.Module / dict files. They do NOT contain any portion
   of Gemma's pre-trained weights. To use them, you must separately load the
   corresponding host-model snapshot (verified by SHA-256 in FINGERPRINT.md).
   These trained artefacts are released under this repository's MIT license.

3. The LeetCode 233 problem statement (in `leetcode233/data/gemma_code_GB01.json`)
   is a publicly listed competitive-programming problem. Problem statements
   themselves are not under copyright in the relevant jurisdictions; the
   particular phrasing in our dataset is the project author's own derivation.

4. The Opus 4.7 chain-of-thought transcript (`leetcode233/data/opus_cot_leetcode233.txt`)
   is a single ~1.4KB excerpt of one Claude Opus 4.7 reply to the LeetCode 233
   problem, used here as reference material for one experiment. The author
   considers this within the scope of educational fair use under applicable
   law. Anthropic's Claude usage is governed by their own terms of service
   (https://www.anthropic.com/legal). If you intend to redistribute or
   commercialise this transcript separately, please review those terms.

5. Five teacher-paired QA templates in `research_steps/teacher_qa_templates/`
   (claudeopusQA01-05.json) were originally generated with Claude Opus 4.6
   for the predecessor project (chenmoacr/amr_wtf, "GHOST"). Same fair-use
   considerations as item 4. The original project does not redistribute
   newer Opus outputs; these templates are kept here only because they are
   the historical bridge between GHOST and this project's GT-template design.
